The paper deals with the construction and analysis of frequency-hopping sequences, which are commonly used in communication systems. This falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of cyclic codes, which are a topic in discrete mathematics and computer science (cs.DS). The analysis of the performance of frequency-hopping sequences involves the use of correlation measures, which is a topic in signal processing and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of frequency-hopping sequences, which is a topic in networked systems and communication protocols (cs.NI).
